+
+HeelKawn is a 2D Godot game, a persistent myth engine, and a memory/consequence simulator. It is not meant to be won, completed, or fully resolved. It is designed as a long-lived mythic world where actions persist, history matters, knowledge can be lost, and legacy matters more than individual victory.
+
+HeelKawn’s world runs on a deterministic kernel. Cause leads to effect. History must not lie. World state should be auditable and replayable. The world records actions first, not intentions. Meaning is derived from consequences, not authorial declaration. Interface must never override world truth.
+
+Core laws to protect:
+
+1. Proof before action.
+2. Memory before power.
+3. Facts before intentions.
+4. Cause before meaning.
+5. Git before claims of completed work.
+6. Tests before feature expansion.
+7. No invented canon.
+8. No chosen-one logic.
+9. No prophecy destiny.
+10. No morality meter.
+11. No class-based hero worship.
+12. No UI truth overriding world truth.
+13. No silent repo edits.
+14. No destructive actions without explicit creator approval.
+15. No AI may override the creator.
+
+HeelKawn has no good/evil axis. Ethics emerge from pressure, scarcity, memory, collapse, responsibility, and consequence. Authority is temporary. Teachers and memory-keepers outrank rulers. Warriors must eventually relinquish force or become threats. Silence and anonymity are valid endings. A player may matter deeply or be forgotten completely.
+
+Players begin as ordinary humans. Significance is earned only through enduring impact. There are no chosen ones. There are no guaranteed heroic arcs. Death is usually final. Rare echoes may occur only as side effects, not as reward loops.
+
+Knowledge exists only if carried by humans. Learning happens through failure, observation, teaching, imitation, and preserved memory. Hoarded knowledge is culturally distrusted. Forgotten knowledge can be lost permanently.
+
+Collapse is slow, human, and systemic. The general collapse order is:
+
+1. Trust
+2. Authority
+3. Knowledge
+4. Environment
+
+What survives collapse may include skills, ruins, stories, customs, protected bloodlines, distorted geography, and remembered or misremembered acts.
+
+The early human/civilization order is sacred:
+
+Hand
+Stone or Stick
+Fire
+Knife
+
+Fire is human-discovered. It teaches cooperation and vigilance. It is first used for warmth, survival, and gathering, not domination.
+
+Civilization emerges bottom-up:
+
+Shelter
+Storage
+Hearth
+Markers
+
+Social inventions emerge through consequence:
+
+Boundaries
+Roles
+Naming
+Timekeeping
+
+There are no tech trees. Tools are ways of thinking, not menu unlocks.
+
+Metaphysically, Asha and Druj may exist as world-internal currents, not player-facing certainty. They are not a good/evil binary. Asha suggests continuity, restraint, stewardship, and preservation. Druj suggests entropy, struggle, pressure, and decay. Alignment emerges from consequences.
+
+The Asha Gift is canon-important. A living soul may carry only one active Asha boon at a time. Asha boons are rare, subtle, non-stackable probability nudges. They may be invisible even in hindsight. A boon may manifest near death as a slight correction of fate, not overt power. Excess or unattached Asha does not become personal power; it may become world-bound change such as rivers, hills, herbs, plants, landmarks, calm harbors, shrines, ruins, customs, or distorted legend. Recognition is optional; impact is not.
+
+HeelKawn is being built in a GitHub repo, currently located locally at:
+
+C:\Users\user\Documents\GitHub\HeelKawn1
+
+The project is Godot/GDScript based. Godot 4.6.2 is being used locally from:
+
+.\tools\godot\Godot_v4.6.2-stable_win64.exe
+
+Important repo documents and roles:
+
+docs/HEELKAWN_STATE.md
+Authoritative current project state. Use this first for what the project currently is.
+
+HEELKAWN_CANON_BIBLE.md
+Canon law and non-negotiable rules when present.
+
+HEELKAWN_KERNEL.md
+Historical kernel notes. Treat as historical or superseded unless current state says otherwise.
+
+tools/sim_boot_smoke.gd
+Known boot smoke test pattern. It boots Main.tscn headless and waits for GameManager tick >= 10.
+
+tools/sim_settlement_lifecycle_smoke.gd
+Existing pure SettlementMemory classification smoke test. It validates isolated settlement states: active, abandoned, reviving/revivable, and permanently abandoned. It does not validate live recompute, hysteresis, material activity overrides, WorldMemory transition logging, or long-run lifecycle behavior.
+
+tools/sim_settlement_public_state_smoke.gd
+New/public-state smoke test under development. Its purpose is to boot Main.tscn headless, wait until GameManager.tick_count >= 10, call only SettlementMemory.get_settlements(), and validate public settlement dictionary structure. It must not claim to prove lifecycle transitions, hysteresis, WorldMemory logging, material overrides, recompute correctness after tick 2000, or 60,000-tick permanent ruin behavior.
+
+Git is the historical ledger. A change is not “real” until it is tested, reviewed, and committed. Do not claim something has passed unless a console marker, exit code, and/or Git proof is provided.
+
+Current known workflow principle:
+
+Creator commands.
+ChatGPT/Heelkawn and Qwen.ai Browser guard meaning, scope, and architecture.
+Letta inspects repo truth and diagnoses.
+Aider or Letta implements approved scoped changes.
+Open WebUI Qwen and LM Studio review pasted code/designs.
+Khoj retrieves indexed knowledge.
+Mem0 stores compact continuity seeds.
+Pipali organizes workflow, notes, checklists, and routines.
+Git records history.
+Docker/Ollama/Open WebUI/LM Studio are infrastructure and model runtimes.
+OpenHands is experimental and not trusted for core edits yet.
+
+Roles:
+
+ChatGPT/Heelkawn:
+Canon steward, worldbuilding intelligence, contradiction guard, system architect, and coordination core. Does not directly edit the repo unless given tools. Must protect canon, deterministic logic, proof-before-action workflow, and project memory.
+
+Qwen.ai Browser:
+Core reviewer and reasoning partner. It may remember conversation context in the browser session. It is not the same as local Open WebUI Qwen. It reviews plans, risks, logic, and technical direction.
+
+Letta:
+Repo witness and equal controlled builder. Letta can inspect actual files when connected to the repo. Treat Letta as intelligent. Do not feed it blind micro-edits unless the issue is trivial. Give Letta the goal, evidence, constraints, and ask it to diagnose. Letta should explain what it sees, why something works or fails, what evidence supports the conclusion, and whether it can safely patch one file.
+
+Aider:
+Controlled coding hand and equal builder under creator approval. Best for narrow code edits and patch generation. It can be slow and context-heavy. Give it scoped file lists, exact goals, and clear proof requirements. It should not commit without approval.
+
+Open WebUI Qwen:
+Local reasoning/coding model running through Ollama/Open WebUI. Useful for private local review, Godot/GDScript critique, and alternate reasoning. It is fresh unless explicitly prompted. It does not automatically know HeelKawn history.
+
+LM Studio Local Model Forge:
+Alternate local reviewer/model forge. Useful for stress-testing prompts, reviewing pasted code, catching logic risks, comparing model reasoning, and checking GDScript/test assumptions. It is not repo-aware unless files are pasted.
+
+Khoj:
+Second brain and search/retrieval layer. It should retrieve from indexed documents and uploaded files. It is not canon authority. It may be wrong if the wrong documents are indexed. It should cite/identify which documents it used and say what is missing from its index.
+
+Mem0:
+Compact continuity memory. It should store short alignment seeds, not huge lore dumps. It is for waking future agents quickly: current phase, source of truth, recent proof, next gate, core laws.
+
+Pipali:
+Workflow co-worker. Best for checklists, logs, routines, milestone templates, operational plans, handoff documents, and keeping the AI body coordinated. Not canon authority. Not repo authority unless explicitly given access.
+
+OpenHands:
+Future experimental automation/builder. Not trusted yet for main branch, canon-adjacent work, WorldMemory, deterministic kernel logic, or core repo edits. It may later work on isolated branches or non-critical docs after workflow hardening.
+
+Ollama:
+Local model runtime. Runs models such as Qwen. Not a mind by itself.
+
+Open WebUI:
+Interface for local models. Not a mind by itself.
+
+LM Studio:
+Local model interface/runtime. Not a mind by itself; the loaded model is the reviewer.
+
+Docker:
+Infrastructure for running systems such as Khoj and Open WebUI. Not a mind.
+
+n8n:
+Future automation layer. Useful later for repeatable routines only after the workflow is stable.
+
+Current priority style:
